title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.2: CHILD PROTECTION SERVICES

description.narrative: Service providers at the state and local levels in UNICEF-targeted areas have strengthened capacities and deliver quality specialized child-protection services with appropriate referral mechanisms in place, which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, more girls and boys are protected from violence, abuse and exploitation and benefit from improved response and prevention systems

title.narrative: Service providers at the state and local levels in UNICEF-targeted areas have strengthened capacities and deliver qualityspecialized child-protection services with appropriate referral mechanisms in place

description.narrative: Specialized services continued to reach vulnerable children across the country. 135,510 children received MHPSS services, and 3,706 unaccompanied and separated children benefited from family tracing and reunification. 274 children (B: 143 & G: 131) were placed in Kafala and 25 were reunified with their families. 23,677 children received GBV services through FCPUs. 2021 witnessed significant decrease in the number of children in institutions indicating the success of UNICEF’s work with justice actors and social welfare institutions, as well as the quality of specialized services. The development and roll-out of multiple standard operating procedures contributed to that change. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:18/01/2022
